      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the replies! I am a bit hesitant to go with the first approach since I don\u0027t quite know about what caused the problem addressed by the comments on https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/skia/src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp?type\u003dcs\u0026q\u003dMacOS+file:%5Esrc/third_party/skia/+package:%5Echromium$\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d815 \n\nI am taking the second approach which presumably more safer since we follow the exact same path as before except for the buggy cases.\n\nFYI, I added a test to demonstrate the problem. Through quite some experiments from last night and this morning, I discovered that for other MacOS (such as 10.14), legacyMakeTypeface without name will return the default font regardless the style. This CL actually fix that as well.",
